FBIS4-19822 "drweu078__a94027" FBIS-WEU-94-076-A Daily Report 21 Apr 1994 ANNEX France Poll Shows Balladur Losing Popularity Poll Shows Balladur Losing Popularity BR1904142494 Paris PARIS MATCH in French 21 Apr 94 pp 86-87--FOR OFFICIAL USE ONLY BR1904142494 Paris PARIS MATCH French BFN [Unattributed report: "`PARIS MATCH -- BVA Opinion Poll: The Fall of Prime Minister Balladur (Down 9 Percent)"] [Text] The latest "PARIS MATCH -- BVA" opinion poll, conducted after the withdrawal of the CIP [youth job training contract] but before the suicide of [President's Mitterrand's adviser] Francois de Grossouvre, shows a real drop in Edouard Balladur's popularity. He has lost 9 percent, posting his worst score since he took office. His popularity rating is negative for the first time and is now below that of Francois Mitterrand. It should be noted that the prime minister's rating has dropped considerably (down 15 percent), compared with people with more centrist views. The government as a whole has been affected by this fall from grace since, also for the first time, the French people -- if they were deputies -- would not support the government in a confidence vote (49 percent no's as opposed to 39 percent yes-votes). As a result of this situation, the Left has gained 3 percent in legislative election voting intentions. The Left-Right balance of power is now 34-44. What is your opinion of Francois Mitterrand as president of the Republic? TOTAL Mar 94 Left voters Right neither Left voters nor Right Good 46 47 78 22 44 Bad 45 46 20 72 41 Don't know 9 7 2 6 15 What is your opinion of Edouard Balladur as prime minister? TOTAL Mar 94 Left voters Right neither Left voters nor Right Good 44 53 21 71 34 Bad 48 38 75 25 55 Don't know 8 9 4 4 11 Are you pleased or displeased with the way France is being governed? TOTAL Mar 94 Left Right neither voters voters Left nor Right Pleased 25 31 15 41 17 Displeased 68 63 81 55 77 Don't Know 7 6 4 4 6 If you were a deputy, would you support Edouard Balladur's government in a confidence vote? TOTAL Mar 94 Left voters Right neither Left voters nor Right Yes 39 43 13 68 29 No 49 43 78 25 55 Don't know 12 14 9 7 16 ---------------------------------------------------------------------------- |For each of the following political figures, state whether or not they ha-| |ve your confidence [figures between parentheses are March 1994 results]. | ---------------------------------------------------------------------------- |Confidence |Change (in pe-|No confidence |No opinion | | | |rcent) | | | | ---------------------------------------------------------------------------- |S. Veil |48 (46) |+ 2 |43 (45) |9 (9) | ---------------------------------------------------------------------------- |E. Balladur |45 (52) |- 7 |48 (42) |7 (6) | ---------------------------------------------------------------------------- |J. Lang |45 (40) |+ 5 |47 (51) |8 (9) | ---------------------------------------------------------------------------- |C. Pasqua |44 (46) |- 2 |48 (45) |8 (9) | ---------------------------------------------------------------------------- |F. Mitterrand |42 (40) |+ 2 |50 (54) |8 (6) | ---------------------------------------------------------------------------- |J. Delors |41 (42) |- 1 |41 (43) |18 (15) | ---------------------------------------------------------------------------- |R. Barre |39 (38) |+ 1 |48 (51) |13 (11) | ---------------------------------------------------------------------------- |F. Leotard |37 (37) |-- |51 (50) |12 (13) | ---------------------------------------------------------------------------- |J. Chirac |36 (36) |-- |55 (57) |9 (7) | ---------------------------------------------------------------------------- |V. Giscard d'-|36 (33) |+ 3 |55 (58) |9 (9) | |Estaing | | | | | ---------------------------------------------------------------------------- |P. Seguin |35 (31) |+ 4 |45 (49) |20 (20) | ---------------------------------------------------------------------------- |B. Tapie33 (27|+ 6 